meta:
  origin:
    producer: World Values Survey Association
    title: World Values Survey (Time-Series)
    description: |-
      The World Values Survey (WVS) is a global research program devoted to the scientific and academic study of social, political, economic, religious and cultural values of people in the world. Since 1981 the WVS has conducted representative national surveys in almost 100 countries in seven waves. The Time-Series (Trend) file pools the repeated cross-sectional surveys from all waves into a single harmonized dataset covering 1981-2022.

      This snapshot contains a selection of questions, collapsed from the WVS Time-Series microdata into weighted country-by-year response shares (the microdata themselves are not redistributed).
    citation_full: |-
      Haerpfer, C., Inglehart, R., Moreno, A., Welzel, C., Kizilova, K., Diez-Medrano, J., Lagos, M., Norris, P., Ponarin, E. & Puranen, B. et al. (eds.). 2024. World Values Survey Time-Series (1981-2022) Cross-National Data-Set. Madrid, Spain & Vienna, Austria: JD Systems Institute & WVSA Secretariat. Data Version 5.0. doi:10.14281/18241.23
    attribution_short: WVS
    version_producer: Version 5.0 (1981-2022)
    url_main: https://www.worldvaluessurvey.org/WVSDocumentationWVL.jsp
    # TODO: confirm the producer's release date of the Time-Series v5.0 file.
    date_published: '2024-06-01'
    date_accessed: '2026-06-30'
    license:
      name: WVSA Conditions of use
      url: https://www.worldvaluessurvey.org/WVSDocumentationWVL.jsp
  is_public: false
